      "id": "m6qvbwz0",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p>\n<p>Statement I : $\\quad \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{Cl}$ will undergo $\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{N}} 1$ reaction though it is a primary halide.</p>\n<p>Statement II : <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6qrrb4j/f507c337-272b-48d4-ae71-3a326ece7e73/a2af6630-e31f-11ef-988c-d59d3feee846/file-jaoe38c1m6qrrb4k.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6qrrb4j/f507c337-272b-48d4-ae71-3a326ece7e73/a2af6630-e31f-11ef-988c-d59d3feee846/file-jaoe38c1m6qrrb4k.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 22nd January Morning Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 35 English\"> will not undergo $\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{N}} 2$ reaction very easily though it is a primary halide.</p>\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "Both Statement I and Statement II are incorrect\n",
        "Both Statement I and Statement II are correct\n",
        "Statement I is correct but Statement II is incorrect\n",
        "Statement I is incorrect but Statement II is correct"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "haloalkanes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
